modules.description: Extracts version strings from Git repositories using `git describe`, with options to control repository location and dirty state. Saves detected version to an OCaml source file, allowing customization of default values and inclusion of system identifiers. Parses OCaml compiler version details into a tuple of integers and a string.

Provides functions to extract the project version from git and write it to an OCaml file. Works with git metadata and string-based version identifiers. Used to automatically generate a version file during build processes.

Extracts and embeds version information from Git repositories, generating OCaml source files with parsed compiler versions and system identifiers. It handles repository paths, dirty state, and custom default values for version strings. Operations include parsing version tuples and writing structured version data. Users can automate version tracking and integrate system-specific details into builds.
